25|$|The {{government}} of the newly formed Union of South Africa began a systematic oppression of <b>black</b> <b>people</b> <b>in</b> South Africa. The Land Act was promulgated in 1913 forcing many non-whites from their farms into the cities and towns to work, and to restrict their movement within South Africa.|$|E
